{
  "page": "Wonders Made by Man",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Titan_of_Braavos.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/7b/Titan_of_Braavos.jpg/300px-Titan_of_Braavos.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"497\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/7b/Titan_of_Braavos.jpg/450px-Titan_of_Braavos.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/7b/Titan_of_Braavos.jpg/600px-Titan_of_Braavos.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Titan_of_Braavos.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <a href=\"/index.php/Titan_of_Braavos\" title=\"Titan of Braavos\">Titan of Braavos</a>, by zippo514 ©</div></div></div>\n<p><i><b>Wonders Made by Man</b></i> is one of two books written by <a href=\"/index.php/Lomas_Longstrider\" title=\"Lomas Longstrider\">Lomas Longstrider</a>, a famous traveler. It records nine man-made wonders of the <a href=\"/index.php/Known_world\" title=\"Known world\">known world</a>, while the second book, <i><a href=\"/index.php/Wonders\" title=\"Wonders\">Wonders</a></i>, records seven natural wonders.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Wonders\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Wonders</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Confirmed_Wonders\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Confirmed Wonders</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Possible_Wonders\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Possible Wonders</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Wonders\">Wonders</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wonders_Made_by_Man&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Wonders\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Confirmed_Wonders\">Confirmed Wonders</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wonders_Made_by_Man&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Confirmed Wonders\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_roads\" title=\"Valyrian roads\">Valyrian roads</a> are listed as the fourth of the nine wonders. Six other wonders have been confirmed, though in unknown order.\n</p><p>The confirmed wonders are:\n</p>\n<ul><li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_roads\" title=\"Valyrian roads\">Valyrian roads</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf721_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf721-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rssm5977.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rssm5977.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Titan_of_Braavos\" title=\"Titan of Braavos\">Titan</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rssm5977.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rssm5977.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Walls_of_Qarth\" title=\"Walls of Qarth\">triple wall</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Qarth\" title=\"Qarth\">Qarth</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Three_bells\" title=\"Three bells\">three bells</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Norvos\" title=\"Norvos\">Norvos</a>, Noom, Narrah, and Nyel.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf822_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf822-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Long_Bridge\" title=\"Long Bridge\">Long Bridge</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>, the longest bridge in the world.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf826_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf826-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/Palace_With_a_Thousand_Rooms\" title=\"Palace With a Thousand Rooms\">Palace With a Thousand Rooms</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Sarnath\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sarnath\">Sarnath</a> (now in ruins after the city was destroyed by the <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki\" title=\"Dothraki\">Dothraki</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf835_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf835-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Possible_Wonders\">Possible Wonders</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wonders_Made_by_Man&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Possible Wonders\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Speculatively, fans have considered the possibility of the <a href=\"/index.php/Hightower\" title=\"Hightower\">Hightower</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a> (the tallest structure in the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>), <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a> (the largest castle in the Seven Kingdoms),<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Five_Forts\" title=\"Five Forts\">Five Forts</a> (massive fortresses along the northeastern boundaries of the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Empire_of_Yi_Ti\" title=\"Golden Empire of Yi Ti\">Golden Empire of Yi Ti</a>) as being among the other man-made wonders.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Citadel1_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Citadel1-10\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>A fourth possibility are the ruins of the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Pyramid_of_Ghis\" title=\"Great Pyramid of Ghis\">Great Pyramid of Ghis</a>, which Lomas is known to have visited.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Lomas is also known to have visited the ruins of the festival city of <a href=\"/index.php/Chroyane\" title=\"Chroyane\">Chroyane</a>, which he describes in the book.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf24.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf24.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> He visited the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Isles\" title=\"Summer Isles\">Summer Isles</a> in search for wonders as well.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf831_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf831-13\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wonders_Made_by_Man&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">It is unlikely that Harrenhal is one of the wonders, because it was only finished in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_before_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_2_Before_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years before Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">2&#160;BC</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf31.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf31.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> while <a href=\"/index.php/Lomas_Longstrider\" title=\"Lomas Longstrider\">Lomas Longstrider</a> likely lived at least some time before that, since he saw the <a href=\"/index.php/Palace_With_a_Thousand_Rooms\" title=\"Palace With a Thousand Rooms\">Palace With a Thousand Rooms</a> before its destruction.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf835_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf835-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wonders_Made_by_Man&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_8\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 8\">Chapter 8</a>, Tyrion III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf721-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf721_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Seven Kingdoms&#58; The Wall and Beyond&#32;(The Night's Watch).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rssm5977.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rssm5977.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rssm5977.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/So_Spake_Martin\" title=\"So Spake Martin\">So Spake Martin</a>: <i><a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.westeros.org/Citadel/SSM/Entry/5977\">Amazon Omniblog Interview</a></i> (January 12, 2012).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_57\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 57\">Chapter 57</a>, Tyrion XI.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf822-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf822_5-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Beyond the Sunset Kingdom&#58; The Free Cities&#32;(Norvos).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf826-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf826_6-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Beyond the Sunset Kingdom&#58; The Free Cities&#32;(Volantis).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf835-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf835_7-0\">7.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf835_7-1\">7.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Beyond the Sunset Kingdom&#58; Beyond the Free Cities&#32;(The Grasslands).</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf31.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf31.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Reign of the Dragons&#58; The Conquest.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Citadel1-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Citadel1_10-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The Citadel: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.westeros.org/Citadel/FAQ/Entry/Which_are_the_16_wonders_of_the_world/\">FAQ - 3.7. Which are the 16 wonders of the world?</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_67\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 67\">Chapter 67</a>, The Kingbreaker.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf24.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf24.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Ancient History&#58; The Long Night.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf831-13\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf831_13-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Beyond the Sunset Kingdom&#58; Beyond the Free Cities&#32;(The Summer Isles).</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403145036\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.051 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.084 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1281/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 9530/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 5966/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 721/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 13/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 1/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 6114/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.020/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 5.38 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   70.410      1 -total\n 42.46%   29.899     13 Template:Ref\n 40.35%   28.412      1 Template:Italic_title\n 31.00%   21.828     13 Template:Ref/core\n 10.67%    7.514      1 Template:Refn\n  7.45%    5.242      2 Template:References\n  5.36%    3.772      1 Template:Date\n  2.79%    1.963      1 Template:Notes\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:8342-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403145036 and revision id 330689\n -->\n",
